<DOCTYPE> MISCELLANEOUS TEXT (slug-filter) </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-13 01:58 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5134 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-FBC-USCNOTES-LADN     10-13 0519
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-USCNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OFFENSE DOESN'T SHIRK BLAME
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC coach Paul Hackett said he didn't mind that
some defensive players began to subtly criticize the offense
following its abysmal performance against Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's frustration. I don't think it's bad to get that out,''
Hackett said. ``If you don't put a loss like that behind you, a
closely fought game, it can do more damage than you realize.''
</P>
<P>
   The defense-vs.-offense issue is not likely to turn into a
conflict this early in the season, because the offense pretty much
agrees with the defense's assessment that it needs to get its act
together.
</P>
<P>
   ``If I played defense, I'd be very frustrated,'' wide receiver
Kareem Kelly said. ``We've got to turn this thing around. Right
now, we're the weak link of the team. When we get in the games, we
don't execute.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't want to point any fingers. I can't block for the line.
I can't throw for the quarterback. I can just worry about catching
the ball.''
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps more troubling for Hackett is that as USC approaches its
sixth game, it still seems in search of an identity.
</P>
<P>
   ``I hoped by midseason, we would have come together and jelled,
but I haven't seen it,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Back to linebacker: Sophomore Darryl Knight's experiment at
tight end has ended. This week, he moved back to his original
position of strongside linebacker. Freshman Aaron Graham has moved
back to middle linebacker after playing at strongside the first
five games.
</P>
<P>
   MacKenzie update: After Tuesday's story in the Daily News that
tailback Malaefou MacKenzie did not go to Arizona because of a team
rules violation, Hackett said there was a miscommunication between
the coaches and MacKenzie, and he left the tailback home to rest
his injured hamstring.
</P>
<P>
   Sources said MacKenzie was left home because he did not suit up
for Oregon State game, when he knew he would be held out.
</P>
<P>
   Line shuffle: With Jason Grain out with a knee injury, Zach
Wilson will start at right guard. Eric Denmon, who was out two
games with sore knees, will start at center against Notre Dame.
Hackett said he would probably start Faasea Mailo at left guard as
Donta Kendrick continues to recover from a sprained ankle.
</P>
<P>
   Fullback Chad Pierson, who has been out since the Hawaii game
with a sprained ankle, is expected to play.
</P>
<P>
   Play-calling progresses: Offensive coordinator Hue Jackson
called the plays against Arizona, although Hackett took over for
the Trojans' final series.
</P>
<P>
   Pants problem: Right before kickoff against Arizona, defensive
line coach Ed Orgeron went to sit down on the team bench and split
his pants.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was thinking, `What do I do?''' Orgeron said.
</P>
<P>
   A USC trainer provided a solution by giving Orgeron a towel
which he wore around his waist during the game.
</P>
<P>
   Stanford game time: USC's game with Stanford on Oct. 23 at the
Coliseum will be at 12:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   It's official: The Butkus Award formally added linebacker Zeke
Moreno to its list of candidates.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-13-99 0158EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19991013.0061 </DOCNO>
