<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ The old man and the old woman
were in their 90s, married 70 years. She had Alzheimer's; he was
still full of verve. And devotion. ``I married a beauty,'' he said.
``And she's still the most beautiful woman in the world.'' As he
leaned over to kiss her, you could see what he meant. You could
envision the young woman he married, and see the beauty still
etched in her face. This scene from a decade ago came back to me,
oddly enough, at a Bruce Springsteen and the E Street Band concert
in Chicago last week. (McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
