<P>
   LIFE IN AMERICA1014: Apples are the main attraction in Miami
Valley
</P>
<P>
   MORROW, Ohio _ On Maplewood Orchards in southern Warren County,
amid an enclave of trees bearing an autumn bounty of red and orange
foliage, Dixie Baker waited for children to experience a small
slice of the family's apple fields. ``This brisk air is what makes
you think of fall, of apples and hay rides,'' Baker said. The
school bus from Milford, a suburb of Cincinnati, finally arrived
and about 30 preschoolers and 15 adults poured onto the Baker's
property. Later, after tours of farming machinery, tiny hands
picked Melrose apples to munch on. The tour is a chance for the
children to get out into the country, said Lisa Robinson, a
schoolteacher. Such curiosity has turned into a worthwhile venture
for orchard growers who have used the apple and other popular
fruits, such as the pumpkin, to draw crowds. (Harris, Dayton Daily
News)
</P>
<P>
