   COOKING-CARDIOLOGIST _ He's the only chef in America with a
whisk-o-scope. ``I wear it to remind people that the fight against
heart disease starts in your kitchen,'' says Dr. Richard Collins,
``the cooking cardiologist.'' Collins came up with the idea of
combining a kitchen whisk and stethoscope and uses his homemade
gadget in cooking lectures and demonstrations. ``I'll try to show
people how they can change recipes into something heart-healthy,''
says Collins, 55, who directs the Alegent Heart Disease Reversal
and Wellness Program at Alegent Health Heart Institute in Omaha,
Neb., and author of a cookbook titled The Cooking
Cardiologist(Advanced Research Press, $21.95). (Dayton Daily News).
MOVED.
