NORTHAM EXPOSURE He's handsome, he's gifted, he's smart, he's on
the verge of becoming a movie star, but British actor Jeremy
Northam wants people to see him as a contemporary guy. Best known
for his portrayals of repressed Englishmen in period films such as
``Emma'' and ``An Ideal Husband,'' he trades in his old-fashioned
costumes for prison stripes in the new comedy ``Happy, Texas.'' By
Merle Ginsberg. From W magazine. 1,000 words.
_____________________________________________________________ 5.
BRUCE WILLIS : BEST AND WORST OF TIMES These are bittersweet times
for Bruce Willis, one of the most prolific of Hollywood's $20
millon men. While his professional life has rarely been better, he
is currently caught up in personal trauma and is separated from his
wife, Demi Moore. While they have not officially divorced, one of
Hollywood's highest-profile marriages appears to be over. Willis
says his character in his new film ``Story of Us'' - a laid-back,
impractical writer - is a lot closer to the real Bruce Willis than
his action-movie persona. By Ivor Davis. 1,500 words + photos. (N/A
Great Britain and Australia.)
