<P>
   CYBORGS-FASHION (New York) _ Thad Starner, a 29-year-old
assistant professor at the Georgia Institute of Technology,
considers himself one of the first cyborgs _ an acronym for
cybernetic organism, a being that is part machine, part human.
Cyborgs wear their computers almost continuously. They get e-mail
on their eyeglasses while they're talking to you, and now they've
recruited models to try to make the idea of wearing a computer, all
day every day, the new thing. A series of fashion shows at a
computer trade show last week gave a glimpse into what happens when
the worlds of technology and fashion try to converge instead of
collide. By Lisa Guernsey.
