</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-MINIS14-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mini views
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``SLC Punk'' (R) _ This energetic, amusing but scattered film
introduces us to Stevo's (Matthew Lillard) world of beer blasts,
punk bands, acid trips and run-ins with the rednecks of Salt Lake
City, circa 1985. A picaresque romp, it wants to be a
``Trainspotting''-lite, an Americanized howl against conformity
that winds up, well, conforming. Grade: C+
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Goodbye Lover'' (R) _ A good film noir _ even a
tongue-in-cheek one, like this wants to be _ has to ground its
hairpin plot with real people. No such luck here. The folks in this
movie, about a sex-death-and-insurance scam, are as slickly remote
as the lavish set decor and cinematography. Grade: C
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Inheritors'' (unrated) _ When a farmer wills his
property to his farmhands, ownership sparks newfound pride in the
peasants. But it also rouses fury from established farmers in this
engaging but uneven Austrian film. In German with English
subtitles. Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Chambermaid on the Titanic'' (unrated) _ The lives of a
French laborer (Olivier Martinez) and his wife (Romane Bohringer)
change forever after his encounter with a chambermaid about to
embark on the Titanic. It's a beguiling meditation on desire, loss
and, especially, the transformative power of art in the drab,
everyday world. Grade: A-
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Rage: Carrie 2'' (R) _ Emily Bergl plays a
misunderstood, telekinetic teen in this cheap, dull horror flick.
The sort-of sequel is so bad, you might mistake it for self-parody.
Amy Irving also stars as the first film's survivor, but skulks
through her scenes looking like she's ready to kill her agent.
(Also available on DVD, with alternate ending, deleted scenes and
audio commentary by director Katt Shea, $24.98.) Grade: D
</P>
<P>
   Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
