 &HT;    Spotlight on William Shakespeare
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   (``10 Things I Hate About You'')
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Shakespeare in Love'' (1998, R). Art imitates life in this
best picture Oscar winner, with Joseph Fiennes, Gwyneth Paltrow and
Judi Dench.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``A Thousand Acres'' (1997, R). King Lear replayed on a
Midwest farm in this family drama starring Jessica Lange, Michelle
Pfeiffer and Jennifer Jason Leigh.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Richard III'' (1995, R). Ian McKellen plays the nasty tyrant
in this fascist-flavored update.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Romeo + Juliet'' (1996, PG-13). Claire Danes and Leonardo
DiCaprio experience that star-crossed love thing in Baz Luhrmann's
Miami Beach transfer.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Hamlet'' (1996, PG-13). Kenneth Branagh's uncut, four-hour
version, with Kate Winslet, Julie Christie and Derek Jacobi.
</P>
<P>
   THE VIDEO COLLECTOR
</P>
