Hirst, an art student full of swagger and energy, decided to put on
a show. He took works by unknown artists, himself and 15 other
students from Goldsmiths College here, and displayed them in a show
called ``Freeze. And so it was that the a new group, the Young
British Artists, was born. By Sarah Lyall.
