<HEADLINE>
THE WELL-DRESSED BORG 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The typical borg outfit consists of three pieces of technology.
The combination is called the Lizzy, after Tin Lizzy, a nickname
for the Ford Model T.
</P>
<P>
   1. THE MONITOR The Private Eye, typically mounted on eyeglasses,
is an optical display that superimposes text onto the view of the
physical scene.
</P>
<P>
   2. THE KEYBOARD The preferred keyboard of borgs, the Twiddler,
is designed to be used in one hand, with the thumb pressing one of
six buttons on the back while the index fingers tap 12 buttons on
the front in various combinations.
</P>
<P>
   3. THE CPU Portable computers for borgs, including wireless
Internet connection, batteries and software (borgs seem to prefer
the Linux operating system), typically have a 133-megahertz chip
and weigh about two pounds.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
