<HEADLINE>
CONCORDE: IF YOU GO 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Flight time: British Air Concordes depart New York's JFK Airport
en route to London/Heathrow daily at 8:45 a.m. and 1:45 p.m., and
from London to New York daily at 10:30 a.m. and 7 p.m. Flight time
is about 3 hours, 15 minutes, compared with about 7 hours, 20
minutes for a subsonic flight. Air France Concordes fly between New
York and Paris.
</P>
<P>
   Fares: Standard fare between New York and London is $5,789 one
way and $10,297 round-trip, with some restrictions. Package deals
can bring down the price dramatically. One of the best, British
Airways' ``Concorde Vacations: London in Style'' package, includes
one way between New York and London on Concorde, the other in
business class, chauffeured limousine airport transfers and three
nights' lodging at a choice of London luxury hotels, including the
Millennium Gloucester, Claridges and the Ritz, for $5,629 to
$6,239, depending on the hotel. Toll-free phone: 877-428-2228.
</P>
<P>
   Those crossing the Atlantic on Cunard Line's QEII can return to
New York on Concorde for an extra $2,395. Phone your travel agent
or Cunard at 800-5-CUNARD.
</P>
<P>
   For more information and reservations: Contact British Airways
at 800-247-9297; www.britishairways.com.
</P>
