<P>
   DELTA _Delta Air Lines Inc. ended its alliance with Swissair AG,
Sabena SA and Austrian Airlines to concentrate on building its new
partnership with Air France SA and AeroMexico.
</P>
<P>
   Delta said the four airlines agreed to honor existing travel
agency and corporate sales agreements through Dec. 31. Flights
ticketed jointly by the carriers will end on Aug. 5, 2000. The end
of the so-called Atlantic Excellence Alliance was anticipated
following Delta's announcement in June that it would link with Air
France. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
