<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-13 17:44 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5769 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e BC-LITERARY-QUIZ-TEX     10-13 0471
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LITERARY-QUIZ-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   This multiple-choice puzzler features distinguished American
authors of the distaff order. You pass with nine correct answers
and earn an A with 12 right.
</P>
<P>
   1. Kate Chopin wrote (a) ``Margaret Howth;'' (b) ``The
Awakening;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   2. Edith Wharton wrote (a) ``The Gods Arrive;'' (b) ``The
Children;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   3. Ellen Glasgow wrote (a) ``The Romantic Comedians;'' (b) ``In
This Our Life;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   4. Willa Cather wrote (a) ``A Girl of the Limberlost;'' (b)
``Janice Meredith;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the
above.
</P>
<P>
   5. Kay Boyle wrote (a) ``Storm;'' (b) ``Avalanche;''' (c) both
of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   6. Pearl Buck wrote (a) ``To Mary, With Love;'' (b) ``Come, My
Beloved;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   7. Lillian Hellman wrote (a) ``The Children's Hour;'' (b) ``Toys
in the Attic;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   8. Edna Ferber wrote (a) ``So Big;'' (b) ``Giant;'' (c) both of
the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   9. Katherine Anne Porter wrote (a) ``Ride the Pink Horse;'' (b)
``Bread and Wine;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the
above.
</P>
<P>
   10. Eudora Welty wrote (a) ``Strange Fruit;'' (b) ``Delta
Wedding;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   11. Joyce Carol Oates wrote (a) ``Just Tell Me What You Want;''
(b) ``Do With Me What You Will;'' (c) both of the above; (d)
neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   12. Joan Didion wrote (a) ``The White Hotel;'' (b) ``The White
Album;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   13. Toni Morrison wrote (a) ``Scarlet Sister Mary;'' (b) ``The
Color Purple;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   14. Margaret Atwood wrote (a) ``Glass People;'' (b) ``The
Handmaid's Tale;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   15. Sue Miller wrote (a) ``Final Payments;'' (b) ``The Good
Mother;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   16. Mona Simpson wrote (a) ``Anywhere but Here;'' (b) ``The
Grab;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   Quiz answers: 1-b; 2-c; 3-c; 4-d; 5-b; 6-b; 7-c; 8-c; 9-d; 10-b;
11-b; 12-b; 13-d; 14-b; 15-b; 16-a. The correct authors for other
works cited are, in order, Rebecca Harding Davis, Gene
Stratton-Porter, Paul Leicester Ford, George R. Stewart, Richard
Sherman, Dorothy Hughes, Ignazio Stallone, Lillian Smith, Jay
Presson Allen, D.M. Thomas, Julia Peterkin, Alice Walker, Gail
Godwin, Mary Gordon and Maria Katzenbach.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
