permanent replacement housing for families who lost their homes.
</P>
<P>
   Caucus members said they will also call on Hollywood to raise
awareness and contribute money to rebuilding efforts.
</P>
<P>
   Rep. Maxine Waters, D-Calif., said she would contact members of
the entertainment community, including producer Quincy Jones,
Motown founder Barry Gordy Jr. and actor Denzel Washington.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have not called on them much in the past, but now is the
time that we need them,'' she said. ``We've got to help each
other.''
</P>
<P>
   (Story can end here. Optional add follows.)
</P>
<P>
   At the press conference, movie actor Bill Duke, whose face is
much more familiar than his name, spoke of the historical
importance of Eastern North Carolina, including Princeville, the
oldest town in the country incorporated by freed slaves.
</P>
<P>
   ``Businesses have been wiped out there, churches, homes and
people are really, really suffering,'' he said. ``I call on all
Americans, particularly my affluent friends in Los Angeles _
producers, actors, writers _to support this effort one thousand
percent.''
</P>
<P>
   Princeville, in Edgecombe County, was submerged in 23 feet of
water for 10 days after Hurricane Floyd. Almost all of the town's
650 homes, 30 businesses and three churches were damaged or
destroyed. The situation is aggravated by the fact that about half
of the residents are senior citizens, who may be too weary and too
poor to start over.
</P>
<P>
   Clayton said that the Caucus wants to help all those hurt by the
floods, including but not limited to disadvantaged communities,
senior citizens and minority communities.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not exclusive,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   At the press conference, Rep. Martin Frost, D-Texas, Democratic
Congressional Campaign Committee chairman, said his party will
fully support relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Black Caucus year in and year out has stood behind the
rest of us when we've asked for help on a variety of things, and
the entire Democratic Caucus wants to be involved in this
project,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
