<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AZR-BUDGET-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, Oct. 14. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
TV-GOODY (Undated) _ It's not like he's never played a doctor
before _ you may remember a little character named Hawkeye Pierce _
but Alan Alda isn't sure why the folks at ``ER'' asked him to hang
a stethoscope around his neck again. By BILL GOODYKOONTZ. Story
will move in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Undated) - One of the all-time greats, a sports
legend in his 60s, died quietly in his home recently. He deserved
in death all the testimonials he'd earned in life, but I had no
plans to produce one. At least, not until Wilt Chamberlain, also in
his 60s, died quietly in his home, and every keyboard puncher in
the Western hemisphere filed a teary-eyed tribute. In our house,
Wilt the Stilt didn't mean nearly as much as Gorilla Monsoon. By EJ
MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
