   (NYT41) WASHINGTON -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- TEST-BAN-TREATY-2, 10-13
-- The Senate on Wednesday rejected a treaty banning all
underground nuclear testing in a 51-48 vote that crushed one of the
major arms initiatives of the Clinton administration. Sens. Trent
Lott, left, the majority leader, and Pete Domenici congratulated
one another on the vote. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
</P>
