JOE-THE-KING-FILM, 10-13 -- Frank Whaley last month at the Empire
Diner in Manhattan; ``Joe the King'' is his directorial debut.
Whaley likes to hear that his film is unsentimental. ``When you're
dealing with something of a personal nature, it's easy to become
precious with it,'' he says. ``Something you might sit at home and
cry about may not be important to the rest of the world.'' (Ozier
Muhammad/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
