<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, OCTOBER 14
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-IRAN-EX-MILITANT-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Oct. 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Oct. 12,
about a reformer in Iran who instigated the seizure of American
hostages misstated the date of the Americans' release and of
President Ronald Reagan's inauguration. It was Jan. 20, 1981, not
1980.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MEMPHIS-MAYOR-NYT (moved on Friday, Oct. 8)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Oct. 8,
about the results of the Memphis mayoral election misspelled the
surname of a political pollster who commented on the results. He is
Steven C. Ethridge, not Etheridge.
</P>
<P>
   BC-EURO-BANK-NYT (moved on Thursday, Oct. 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Oct. 7,
about Sweden's success in preserving a welfare state while also
embracing entrepreneurship and unrestricted competition misspelled
the name of an industrial park started by Ericsson and I.B.M. in
the 1970's. It is the Kista Science Park, not Kiska.
</P>
