<P>
   (NYT45) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-4, 10-13
-- As seen through the legs of Scott Brosius of the New York
Yankees (while he rounds the bases), Troy O'Leary of the Boston Red
Sox unsuccessfully climbs the wall as Brosius' two run home run
escapes the park in the second inning of Game 1 of the American
League Championship Series on Wednesday. (Barton Silverman/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT44) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-3, 10-13
-- Orlando Hernandez of the New York Yankees displays his unique
pitching delivery in the first inning of Game 1 of the American
League Championship Series against the Boston Red Sox on Wednesday
in the Bronx. (Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT43) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-3
-- Paul O'Neill of the New York Yankees grounding to Jose Offerman
of the Boston Red Sox in the first inning of Game 1 of the American
League Championship Series on Wednesday in the Bronx. Offerman
bobbled the ball and O'Neill, playing with a broken rib, was safe.
(Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT42) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-1, 10-13
-- Nomar Garciaparra of the Boston Red Sox throwing out Chuck
Knoblauch of the New York Yankees in the first inning of Game 1 of
the American League Championship Series on Wednesday in the Bronx.
(Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
