<TEXT>
<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos have been added to
tonight's New York Times Photo Package, moving 10/13/99. Photo
clients will automatically receive these photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
(888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT51) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- SUB-BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-8,
10-13 -- Scott Brosius of the New York Yankees colliding with
catcher Jason Varitek of the Boston Red Sox at home plate in the
seventh inning of Game 1 of the American League Championship Series
on Wednesday. Varitek dropped the ball just before Brosius arrived
home on a single by Derek Jeter to even the score 3-3. (Barton
Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT50) ATLANTA -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBN-METS-BRAVES-8, 10-13 --
Manager Bobby Valentine of the New York Mets looks exasperated near
the end of a 4-3 loss to the Atlanta Braves in Game 2 of the
National League Championship Series on Wednesday. The victory gave
Atlanta a 2-0 lead in the best-of-seven series. (Frank
Niemeir/Atlanta Journal-Constitution Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT49) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-7, 10-13
-- Derek Jeter of the New York Yankees tagging out Darren Lewis of
the Boston Red Sox trying to steal second base in the sixth inning
of Game 1 the American League Championship Series on Wednesday.
(Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT48) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-6, 10-13
-- Trot Nixon of the the Boston Red Sox winces in pain after diving
and missing on a triple by Scott Brosius of the New York Yankees in
the fourth inning of Game 1 of the American League Championship
Series on Wednesday. (Bill Greene/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT47) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-5, 10-13
-- Catcher Jason Varitek of the the Boston Red Sox dives but fails
to catch a foul ball as hit by Chuck Knoblauch of the New York
Yankees in the first inning of Game 1 of the American League
Championship Series on Wednesday. An amused Mayor Rudolph W.
Giuliani, in a Yankees cap, looks on. (Barry Chin/Boston Globe
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT46) WASHINGTON -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- TREATY-MISSTEPS, 10-13 --
An ardent foe of the nuclear test ban treaty, Sen. Jesse Helms,
R-N.C., returns to his office after Wednesday night's vote. The
Senate rejected the treaty banning all underground nuclear testing
in a 51-48 vote that crushed one of the major arms initiatives of
the Clinton administration. (Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT45) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-4, 10-13
-- As seen through the legs of Scott Brosius of the New York
Yankees (while he rounds the bases), Troy O'Leary of the Boston Red
Sox unsuccessfully climbs the wall as Brosius' two run home run
escapes the park in the second inning of Game 1 of the American
League Championship Series on Wednesday. (Barton Silverman/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT44) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-3, 10-13
-- Orlando Hernandez of the New York Yankees displays his unique
pitching delivery in the first inning of Game 1 of the American
League Championship Series against the Boston Red Sox on Wednesday
in the Bronx. (Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT43) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-2, 10-13
-- Paul O'Neill of the New York Yankees grounding to Jose Offerman
of the Boston Red Sox in the first inning of Game 1 of the American
League Championship Series on Wednesday in the Bronx. Offerman
bobbled the ball and O'Neill, playing with a broken rib, was safe.
(Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT42) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-1, 10-13
-- Nomar Garciaparra of the Boston Red Sox throwing out Chuck
Knoblauch of the New York Yankees in the first inning of Game 1 of
the American League Championship Series on Wednesday in the Bronx.
(Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
